[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":189},["ShallowReactive",2],{"post":3,"content-query-nk0FdnuyGi":118},{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"title":8,"description":9,"imagesource":10,"imagecredit":10,"image":11,"createdAt":12,"updatedAt":12,"readingTime":13,"body":16,"_type":112,"_id":113,"_source":114,"_file":115,"_stem":116,"_extension":117},"/posts/debian-tracker-miner-store-high-disk-io","posts",false,"","Debian Jessie high disk I/O","A potential fix for anybody experiencing very high disk I/O on the latest Debian or Ubuntu.",null,"2015.08.02T060000_debian-tracker-miner-store-high-disk-io.png","2015-08-02T06:00:00",{"text":14,"minutes":15,"time":15,"words":15},"0 min read",0,{"type":17,"children":18,"toc":109},"root",[19,27,32,54,59,94,99,104],{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":22,"children":23},"element","p",{},[24],{"type":25,"value":26},"text","Hi all,",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":28,"children":29},{},[30],{"type":25,"value":31},"I've been having issues lately with Debian Jessie having insanely high disk I/O. My iowait was at between 15 and 30%, disk utilisation was permanently at 100% - my poor HDD! More importantly, it made the machine pretty unresponsive if I needed to run VMs, editor and browser at the same time. Not the performance I expect from an i7!",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":33,"children":34},{},[35,37,43,45,52],{"type":25,"value":36},"After some investigation (mainly using iostat and ps -eo), it appeared to be programs prefixed with ",{"type":20,"tag":38,"props":39,"children":40},"i",{},[41],{"type":25,"value":42},"tracker-",{"type":25,"value":44}," that were the culprits. The information I ",{"type":20,"tag":46,"props":47,"children":49},"a",{"href":48},"https://wiki.gnome.org/Projects/Tracker",[50],{"type":25,"value":51},"found about Tracker",{"type":25,"value":53}," made it sound pretty nifty, but definitely not a fixed requirement for using Gnome. I don't really use the file search features of the Gnome overlay anyway, and I don't tend to search for files using the UI either - so I figured it's probably safe enough to disable it and see how things go.",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":55,"children":56},{},[57],{"type":25,"value":58},"To disable it, you will want to run the tracker-properties application. You can either type that into a terminal, or type \"tracker\" into the overlay, and select Search & Indexing. I unchecked the following options:",{"type":20,"tag":60,"props":61,"children":62},"ul",{},[63,69,74,79,84,89],{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":65,"children":66},"li",{},[67],{"type":25,"value":68},"Indexing: Monitor file and directory changes",{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":70,"children":71},{},[72],{"type":25,"value":73},"Indexing: Enable when running on battery",{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":75,"children":76},{},[77],{"type":25,"value":78},"Indexing: Enable for initial data population",{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":80,"children":81},{},[82],{"type":25,"value":83},"Locations: All of them",{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":85,"children":86},{},[87],{"type":25,"value":88},"Control: Index content of files found (this is most likely to have been the issue, as I have a number of large VMs on this partition)",{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":90,"children":91},{},[92],{"type":25,"value":93},"Control: Index numbers",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":95,"children":96},{},[97],{"type":25,"value":98},"After applying these changes, I opened it back up and went to the System tab. This page allows you to remove all old indexed data. I chose to do so, but I don't think it's likely this will achieve much.",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":100,"children":101},{},[102],{"type":25,"value":103},"Almost immediately after making these changes, my disk spun down, my computer started being responsive again, and I could get back to work in peace!",{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":105,"children":106},{},[107],{"type":25,"value":108},"That's all for today, I just wanted to post this in case it helps anybody else who's experiencing similar issues.",{"title":7,"searchDepth":110,"depth":110,"links":111},2,[],"markdown","content:posts:2015-08-02-debian-tracker-miner-store-high-disk-io.md","content","posts/2015-08-02-debian-tracker-miner-store-high-disk-io.md","posts/2015-08-02-debian-tracker-miner-store-high-disk-io","md",{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"title":8,"description":9,"imagesource":10,"imagecredit":10,"image":11,"createdAt":12,"updatedAt":12,"readingTime":119,"body":120,"_type":112,"_id":113,"_source":114,"_file":115,"_stem":116,"_extension":117},{"text":14,"minutes":15,"time":15,"words":15},{"type":17,"children":121,"toc":187},[122,126,130,144,148,175,179,183],{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":123,"children":124},{},[125],{"type":25,"value":26},{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":127,"children":128},{},[129],{"type":25,"value":31},{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":131,"children":132},{},[133,134,138,139,143],{"type":25,"value":36},{"type":20,"tag":38,"props":135,"children":136},{},[137],{"type":25,"value":42},{"type":25,"value":44},{"type":20,"tag":46,"props":140,"children":141},{"href":48},[142],{"type":25,"value":51},{"type":25,"value":53},{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":145,"children":146},{},[147],{"type":25,"value":58},{"type":20,"tag":60,"props":149,"children":150},{},[151,155,159,163,167,171],{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":152,"children":153},{},[154],{"type":25,"value":68},{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":156,"children":157},{},[158],{"type":25,"value":73},{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":160,"children":161},{},[162],{"type":25,"value":78},{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":164,"children":165},{},[166],{"type":25,"value":83},{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":168,"children":169},{},[170],{"type":25,"value":88},{"type":20,"tag":64,"props":172,"children":173},{},[174],{"type":25,"value":93},{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":176,"children":177},{},[178],{"type":25,"value":98},{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":180,"children":181},{},[182],{"type":25,"value":103},{"type":20,"tag":21,"props":184,"children":185},{},[186],{"type":25,"value":108},{"titl